<TITLE> Photos, writings on Aila sufferings published </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 21 (bdnews24.com) -- A compilation of write-ups and photographs by 15 journalists of their firsthand exposure to the sufferings of Aila-affected people over the last one year was published on Friday. Environment and forest secretary Mihir Kanti Majumder and Baishakhi Television's chief news editor Monjurul Ahsan Bulbul jointly unwrapped the publication at the National Press Club. Majumder spoke of the government's initiative to reforest a 7000-kilometre stretch along the coastal dykes to 'help fight natural calamities'. He also said that initiatives will be taken to involve people in the coastal areas in the preservation and repairs of coastal embankments. The cyclone Aila hit the country's coast on May 25 last year. Campaign for Sustainable Rural Livelihoods (CSRL) and Emergency Capacity Building Project made the compilation of the writings and photographs by 15 journalists of national and international TV, newspapers and agencies. Associated Press (AP) country correspondent Julhas Alam, European Press Photo Agency (EPA)'s Bangladesh bureau photographer Abir Abdullah and other representatives of international and national television, newspapers and agencies spoke at the programme. bdn
